{
  "act_id": "act_calculation",
  "title": "Calculating the Range",
  "viz_panel": "svg",
  "beats": [
    {
      "say": "Now for the final calculation. To find where this arrow lands, we need the total time of flight — how long it stays airborne.",
      "card": {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "Finding the range requires calculating the total flight time first"
      }
    },
    {
      "say": "The arrow returns to ground level when its height y equals zero. That's our key insight for solving this problem.",
      "card": {
        "type": "latex",
        "content": "y = 0 \\text{ when arrow hits ground}",
        "highlight": true
      },
      "viz_actions": [
        {
          "method": "showKinematicEquation",
          "params": {
            "equation": "vertical"
          },
          "offset": "+0.5"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "say": "Using the kinematic equation for vertical motion: y equals initial vertical velocity times t, minus one-half g t squared. Set this equal to zero.",
      "card": {
        "type": "derivation",
        "title": "Time of Flight Equation",
        "steps": [
          {
            "latex": "y = v_{0y}t - \\frac{1}{2}gt^2"
          },
          {
            "latex": "0 = 20t - \\frac{1}{2}(9.8)t^2",
            "highlight": true
          },
          {
            "latex": "0 = 20t - 4.9t^2"
          }
        ]
      },
      "viz_actions": [
        {
          "method": "solveEquation",
          "params": {
            "steps": "setup"
          },
          "offset": "+1.0"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "say": "Factor out t: t times quantity twenty minus four point nine t equals zero. So either t equals zero — that's launch — or twenty minus four point nine t equals zero. Solving: t equals four point zero eight seconds.",
      "card": {
        "type": "derivation",
        "title": "Solving for Time",
        "steps": [
          {
            "latex": "t(20 - 4.9t) = 0"
          },
          {
            "latex": "t = 0 \\text{ or } 20 - 4.9t = 0"
          },
          {
            "latex": "t = \\frac{20}{4.9} = 4.08 \\text{ seconds}",
            "highlight": true
          }
        ]
      },
      "viz_actions": [
        {
          "method": "highlightTimeOfFlight",
          "params": {
            "t": 4.08
          },
          "offset": "+1.2"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "say": "Range equals horizontal velocity times time. We have thirty-four point six meters per second horizontally, times four point zero eight seconds. That gives us one hundred forty-one meters.",
      "card": {
        "type": "derivation",
        "title": "Final Range Calculation",
        "steps": [
          {
            "latex": "\\text{Range} = v_x \\times t"
          },
          {
            "latex": "= 34.6 \\times 4.08"
          },
          {
            "latex": "= 141 \\text{ meters}",
            "highlight": true
          }
        ]
      },
      "viz_actions": [
        {
          "method": "calculateRange",
          "params": {
            "formula": "distance"
          },
          "offset": 0
        },
        {
          "method": "drawRangeMeasurement",
          "params": {
            "style": "groundLine"
          },
          "offset": "+1.5"
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}